South African 10-year borrowing
costs declined at an auction today.  The central bank sold 1 billion rand of 6.75 percent bonds
due 2021 at a yield of 7.96 percent, the central bank said in a
statement on its page on Bloomberg today. That compares with
8.42 percent on July 19. It also sold 1.1 billion rand of 7
percent debt due 2031 at 8.47 percent compared with 8.25 percent
at the previous sale on Aug. 30.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ana Monteiro at 
 amonteiro4@bloomberg.net  